##Experts urge caution to release prevention information, but don't believe in "effective drugs"

I-CAIJING

CAIJING magazine official Wechat. "CAIJING" magazine, sponsored by the China Securities Market Research Center, was first published in 1998, adhering to the news concept of "independence, exclusiveness and originality" , and is known for authoritative, impartial and professional reporting, it is a must-read publication for policy-makers, researchers and managers in the field of politics and economics.

The following article was written by Zhao Tianyu

Linkage of three medical, bridge capital, direct health

The screening of drugs and vaccines, a much-anticipated event, also requires accurate information to reduce public misunderstanding

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo / Xinhua

By Zhao Tianyu, CAIJING

Editor | Wang Xiao

On February 25,2020, a new "effective drug" for treating new pneumonia —— The new oral vaccine -- was launched.

The news came from the Tianjin Mobile New Media Platform "Jinyun" Weibo, which said that Professor Huang Jinhai's team from the College of life sciences of Tianjin University has developed a new oral protective agent for coronavirus, namely an oral vaccine.

Tianjin University Propaganda Department a staff member's mobile phone therefore news, in the same day morning by the media to shut down.

"The follow-up results are hard to say at the moment, and no further progress has been made, " another person from the Publicity Department of Tianjin University told Caijing. "The gold sea team's vaccine research and development has only made a preliminary progress. " Is the preliminary results, from the public application still need a long process, the need for rigorous scientific proof.

New Crown outbreak has been nearly two months, related drugs, vaccine information emerge one after another. All sides are trying to find effective drugs, but from the initial scramble for Shuanghuanglian oral liquid farce, to now, the authority information is still insufficient.

As of February 24, "CAIJING" reporter inquiries, at least 225 new pneumonia drugs, treatment of clinical trials have been registered. In addition to some of the drugs and vaccines that have not yet been tested in clinical trials and have been declared "effective" , the drug market under the epidemic has frequently reversed whether the drugs are effective or not.

The World Health Organization (WHO) states on its Web site, "there is currently no specific drug to recommend preventive or therapeutic COVID-19. "

Researcher Cao Bin, Deputy Director of the china-japan Friendship Hospital and a member of the expert panel of the National Health Commission, said recruiting patients is now harder, WHO senior adviser Bruce Aylward said at a Feb. 24 press conference, not only are there fewer cases, but many other drugs are being tested at the same time, and those drugs don't seem to hold much hope.

February 24, the State Council response to new pneumonia epidemic joint prevention and control mechanism of the Scientific Research Team (hereinafter referred to as the scientific research team) announced the news of clinical research norms. If the test group has obvious side effects, or no clear treatment effect, immediately report to the medical institutions, medical institutions early termination of the study, and promptly report to the joint prevention and control mechanism research team.

Medicine is a commodity, with business logic and profit behind it, whether it comes or not. In an epidemic, if a drug is said to be effective, local procurement can be accelerated in the production and marketing of green light on the road, the pharmaceutical company's revenue, brand, social responsibility, public image, are beneficial. Because of this, the release of drug, vaccine information should be extra cautious.

At the same time, the scientific research team encourages the use of drugs with definite efficacy, which should be promoted so as to benefit more patients as soon as possible.

"It's good to give people a little hope, I'm not against it, but it's better to be serious, " said Taurina, an expert on vaccines and immunization programs.

Are Drugs and vaccines effective

According to the source, Golden Sea itself has taken four times the amount of the new coronavirus oral vaccine samples, said No side effects.

The Tianjin University Propaganda Department said the announcement was made in the hope of finding qualified companies to cooperate in promoting vaccine development.

The vaccine, developed by the Golden Sea team, uses food grade safe SACCHAROMYCES CEREVISIAE as its carrier and COVID-19 s protein as its target to produce antibodies. "It is estimated to be similar to the original Lanjunjing, but not a vaccine, " a vaccine expert from China's Disease Control System told CAIJING.

Chen Kaixian, a member of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and a vaccine expert, explained at a press conference that the process of vaccine development includes the steps of obtaining immunogens, testing the immune response, conducting toxicological studies and other preliminary research and development stages, as well as registration of Vaccine Research and development, this included a series of clinical studies. "So it's a process, it's going to take a long time, " he said.

At this stage, it is clearly too early to confirm the efficacy of this new oral coronavirus preparation.

According to the Golden Sea Interpretation, the team is currently actively deployed in animal toxicology, immune efficacy, pilot production and other evaluations. That said, it's a long way from large-scale validation of safe, effective, and final use.

In the nearly two months since the new crown outbreak, similar misinformation and misunderstandings have occurred many times.

A 44-year-old woman living in Zhengzhou was diagnosed with new coronary pneumonia on February 14. Looking back, she did not go out on February 1, February 2, she walked to a pharmacy to buy "Shuanghuanglian oral liquid" , then said she did not go out, February 13, feeling unwell, to Zhengzhou Central Hospital, diagnosed the next day. The news came from Zhengzhou, the official microblog of the Propaganda Department of the Zhengzhou Municipal Party Committee. The case number was 144. "Ironic, " read one of the most popular comments on the message.

The so-called "effective medicine" against the new coronavirus, which has caused confusion and suspicion to the public, was first given by Shuanghuanglian oral liquid.

"The Shanghai Institute of Medicine and Wuhan Institute of Virology jointly discovered that Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, a Chinese patent medicine, can inhibit COVID-19, " the news came out, out of trust in professional scientific research institutions, people all over the country queued overnight to buy Shuanghuanglian oral liquid.

Xuzhou, in Jiangsu Province, was not at the heart of the new crown outbreak, even though there were queues outside pharmacies where Shuanghuanglian was also sold out. "CAIJING" reporters learned that Shuanghuanglian in the cold medicine was not a hot variety, the store inventory is not much, soon out of stock, this more aggravated the panic buying psychology of the public.

However, this is an unclinically proven drug message. When asked about the data from the previous phase of the clinical trial, the relevant person from the Shanghai Institute of Medicine of the Chinese Academy of Sciences replied that, "I don't have one, I don't know, I can't answer that question right now, " a spokesman for the Shanghai Institute of Medicine said. "This conclusion is based on the results of in vitro studies in the laboratory. " Further clinical studies are needed to confirm this.

Zhuo Yongqing, a distinguished researcher at the Tsinghua University School of Law, disagreed. "What evidence would make him talk like that? " He questioned.

Since then, the industry has generally advised not to take drugs for nothing. But not long after that, another "flickering" drug appeared, Abidor.

ABIDOR dates back to the former Soviet Union and is used primarily as a treatment for influenza. On Feb. 4, Li Lanjuan, an academician of the Chinese Academy of Engineering and a member of the National Health Commission's High Level Expert Group, announced in Wuhan the preliminary results of Arbidol's treatment of new coronavirus pneumonia, which showed in vitro cell experiments, aBIDOR compared with the control group, "can effectively inhibit coronaviruses up to 60 times, and significantly inhibit the virus on the cellular effects. ".

Academician Li Lanjuan proposed that Abidor be included in the sixth edition of the COVID-19. On February 19th the proposal was adopted.

ABIDOR suddenly became popular, and even manufacturers "stunned, " told CAIJING: "Very surprised. "

The reverse is coming fast. Two days later, 10 authors from the Department of infection and immunology, Shanghai Municipal Clinical Center for public health, studied 134 patients with new coronavirus pneumonia and retrospectively analyzed the course of clinical treatment of these patients. The conclusion was that Arbidol was not found to improve symptoms or shorten the turnaround time of respiratory specimens, and that the efficacy of the drug in the treatment of COVID-19 pneumonia "remains to be evaluated further" .

At the same time, the study also analyzed the efficacy of Lopinavitornavir in the treatment of new coronary pneumonia, the conclusion is the same. Although also included in the NCP protocol, Lopinavitonavir was introduced earlier and has been recommended for trial since the beginning. The study has been published in the Chinese Journal of Infectious Diseases.

Drug Selection and information release can not be arbitrary

At present, the medical community is recognized that the drug through clinical trials for verification of the whole process.

Chemicals go through a long process of validation before they are allowed to be taken by humans. The study of drug prescription composition, technology, pharmacy, pharmacy, pharmacology and toxicology, including animal experiments. After the preliminary determination of the drug, the third phase clinical trial of the human body will be conducted, the Main Verification Safety, curative effect, Side Effect Safety and usage and so on.

After all the steps are passed, the drug can be sent to the Drug Regulatory Department for approval before it is put on the market. By contrast, none of the drugs now touted as "effective" in treating NCP have gone through the process.

In the face of the specific nature of the disaster, Li shuting, Secretary General of the Public Welfare Fund for Clinical Research, told Caijing that the availability of these available drugs during the epidemic was based on urgent clinical needs, "We are dealing with a completely new virus, and there is no drug on the market for this virus, " he said. At this point, if there are drugs with the same mechanism or proven efficacy in vitro, they can be tested in humans, in line with ethical requirements.

As of February 24,225 clinical trials of new coronavirus drugs and therapies had been registered on the website of the China Clinical Trial Registration Center, involving high-sounding drugs such as Fabiravir and chloroquine phosphate, there are also Shuanghuanglian oral solution, Tanreqing injection and other traditional Chinese medicine.

A clinical trial was registered on February 2 to study the effects of Taijiquan on pulmonary function and quality of life in convalescent patients with new coronary pneumonia. Another clinical trial, registered on February 18th, on a similar subject, studied the Health Qigong nourishing lung formula.

"If the Chinese trial design does not have rigorous parameters, such as control groups, randomized trials and measures of clinical outcomes, then these efforts will be in vain, " said Soumya Swaminathan, chief scientist at the World Health Organization (WHO) , the team has been evaluating many trials in China and drawing up plans for a clinical trial that could be conducted simultaneously by clinicians around the world.

Soumya Swaminathan says the WHO is working with Chinese scientists to develop standards. For example, a person's recovery or deterioration in the course of a disease should be measured in the same way regardless of the treatment he or she receives.

As the development of new drugs takes too long and the epidemic of new pneumonia can not wait, looking for drugs from the perspective of efficiency, "new use of old drugs" is a way to screen out potential drugs from existing ones, and then come to a conclusion whether it's effective or not.

Even companies specialising in early-stage screening can not easily say which drugs "will work" . Zhang Peiyu, chief scientist of Jingtai Technology, told Caijing that since the outbreak began, the company has been using artificial intelligence and computational chemistry to screen drugs and constantly whittle down candidates. "It's really not convenient for us to say which drug is most likely, just to avoid misleading people, " he said, adding that caution should be exercised "until the drug is proven, or even ready for clinical trials. ".

Although we have a long list of studies, we also emphasize that research projects should be prioritized, WHO director general senior adviser Bruce Aylward said at a press conference on February 24, in order to quickly grasp the knowledge to further block the spread of the virus, to further reduce the rate of severe illness and mortality. "We believe Jusix Wedde may have the desired effect. " .

On the same day, the above-mentioned research team issued a paper, the efficacy of clear drugs should promote the use of drugs as soon as possible, so as to benefit more patients as soon as possible.

Based on what criteria?

Not only is there a new outbreak of pneumonia, but many diseases have an official treatment plan, with chapters covering disease testing, drug and therapy recommendations, leading doctors to treat patients in a scientific and rational manner.

As of 24 February, the protocol for the diagnosis and treatment of NCP has been updated to the sixth edition, which is to be followed by medical institutions throughout the country.

The sixth edition is a revision of the diagnosis and treatment plan by experts from the National Health Commission and the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine, based on the analysis, evaluation and summary of the pre-treatment work.

What exactly is the screening criteria for drugs remains unclear; why do some drugs make it into treatment plans and why don't others? No explanation has been given by the author or publisher.

The first-line hospital in the treatment of patients, will be based on the diagnosis and treatment program to make some adjustments. Experts from Tongji Hospital, affiliated to Tongji Medical College, released the hospital's quick guide to diagnosis and treatment on Jan. 21, based on first line clinical experience and the National Health and Safety Commission's diagnosis and treatment plan, it's been updated several times since.

"It's normal to have a small difference, " said Zhao Jianping, head of the Wuhan Medical Care Team.

It's clear that the treatment plan is having an effect on drug sales and visibility. During the outbreak, people were quarantined from their homes and rarely went out. Business at pharmacies was down, and sales weren't what they used to be.

Lianhua Qingwen is also a traditional Chinese medicine, appeared very early in the diagnosis and treatment of new coronary pneumonia, as a medical observation period of one of the recommended proprietary Chinese medicine. Hanlin General Manager Pang Zihan told the "financial" reporter, Lianhua Qingwen has become one of the few hot-selling drugs.

Manufacturers of Lianhua Qingwen, a traditional Chinese medicine, used the opportunity to reap dividends, such as 002603.Sz  , which rose by the daily limit as early as January 20, shortly after the outbreak of the new crown disease. The company's share price is also significantly higher than before the outbreak.

The diagnosis and treatment plan during the SARS epidemic, how to describe drugs, how to screen, may be a reference. On September 30,2003, the Chinese Medical Journal published the Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome, which had been written by a team headed by Zhong Nanshan. This edition has been written, "in the diagnosis and treatment, especially treatment, as far as possible to bring together the consensus of experts, and clinical efficacy is not yet certain prevention and treatment methods are not recommended. "

On May 25,2005, the former Ministry of Health and the State Administration of Traditional Chinese Medicine issued a notice to update the diagnosis and treatment plan for SARS (2004 edition) . As indicated in this edition, no Specific drug for the SARS virus has been found. Retrospective analysis of clinical data showed that Welling and other commonly used antiviral drugs were ineffective against SARS.

More than a decade on, COVID-19, medical experts warn, there is still no cure, only trial and error, and efficiency is higher than ever thanks to advances in technology. But the problem remains clear: Without a single standard for drug screening, relying solely on experts, agencies, or on individual cases to determine whether a drug is effective, there could be more hype, it is also not conducive to the first-line medical staff to arrange a reasonable treatment program.

The industry generally believes that drug screening, such a much-anticipated event, the need to accurately convey information in order to reduce public misunderstanding. No more word play in the race between new CAP treatment and research.

(China business reporter Xin NA contributed to this report.)
